%global packname  splitTools
%global packver   0.2.0
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          0.2.0
Release:          1%{?dist}
Summary:          Tools for Data Splitting

License:          GPL (>= 2)
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel >= 3.5.0
Requires:         R-core >= 3.5.0
BuildArch:        noarch
BuildRequires:    R-stats 
Requires:         R-stats 

%description
Fast, lightweight toolkit for data splitting. Data sets can be partitioned
into disjoint groups (e.g. into training, validation, and test) or into
(repeated) k-folds for subsequent cross-validation. Besides basic splits,
the package supports stratified, grouped as well as blocked splitting.
Furthermore, cross-validation folds for time series data can be created.
See e.g. Hastie et al. (2001) <doi:10.1007/978-0-387-84858-7> for the
basic background on data partitioning and cross-validation.

